---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';

// One-pager PDF lives at public/downloads/edward-roske-speaker-onepager.pdf.
// Regenerate via: python scripts/build-speaker-onepager.py
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Book Edward Roske to Keynote | Roske.AI"
  description="Book Edward Roske for your conference, corporate offsite, or executive event. Keynotes on AI, finance, and the Office of the CFO. Twenty-five years on stage. Fifty countries. Seven continents."
  ogImage="/images/hero-speaking.png">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative py-20 md:py-28 px-6 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 dark:block hidden bg-gradient-to-b from-[var(--color-bg)] to-[var(--color-surface)]"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 dark:hidden block bg-gradient-to-b from-[var(--color-bg-light)] to-gray-50"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center gap-10 lg:gap-16">
        <div class="flex-1 max-w-2xl text-center lg:text-left">
          <p class="text-sm font-[var(--font-mono)] tracking-widest uppercase mb-4 text-[var(--color-accent)]"
            style="animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out forwards;">
            Speaking
          </p>
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black tracking-tight leading-tight mb-6 dark:text-white text-[var(--color-primary)]"
            style="animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 0.1s forwards; opacity: 0; font-family: var(--font-heading);">
            Questions, not predictions.
          </h1>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed mb-8 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]"
            style="animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 0.2s forwards; opacity: 0;">
            A keynote for CFOs, CEOs, and the boards who report to them. Twenty-five years inside the Office of the CFO. A master's in data science. Fifteen books written from 2007 to today. And a podcast built entirely around the questions executives are quietly asking themselves about AI.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 justify-center lg:justify-start"
            style="animation: fadeInUp 0.6s ease-out 0.3s forwards; opacity: 0;">
            <a href="#inquiry"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent)] text-white font-medium hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)] transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
              Book Edward
            </a>
            <a href="/meet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-medium transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5
                dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-white dark:hover:bg-white/10 dark:border dark:border-white/10
                bg-black/5 text-[var(--color-primary)] hover:bg-black/10 border border-black/10">
              Screening Call (30 min)
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-shrink-0" style="animation: fadeInUp 0.8s ease-out 0.3s forwards; opacity: 0;">
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="absolute -inset-4 rounded-2xl bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 blur-2xl"></div>
            <img src="/images/hero-speaking.png"
              alt="Edward Roske giving a keynote on a TED Talk stage with AI + FINANCE displayed behind him"
              class="relative rounded-2xl w-full max-w-md lg:max-w-lg shadow-2xl ring-1 ring-white/10"
              loading="eager" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stats strip -->
  <Section dark>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 text-center">
      {[
        { value: "50+", label: "Countries Spoken In" },
        { value: "7", label: "Continents" },
        { value: "300+", label: "Keynotes & Sessions" },
        { value: "25+", label: "Years on Stage" },
      ].map(stat => (
        <div class="animate-on-scroll">
          <div class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-[var(--color-accent)] mb-2">{stat.value}</div>
          <div class="text-sm dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)] font-medium">{stat.label}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Why Book Edward -->
  <Section title="Why Book Edward" subtitle="A speaker who's done the work the audience is asking about.">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Twenty-five years in the Office of the CFO">
          <p>Founded interRel at twenty-two, ran it for twenty-five years as one of the longest-standing Oracle Platinum EPM Partners, and merged it into Argano, a billion-dollar consulting firm. The audience's planning, consolidation, and analytics problems are problems Edward has actually shipped solutions for.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="A data scientist, not a futurist">
          <p>Master of Data Science from SMU (perfect 4.0 GPA, Outstanding Graduate). Currently building MCP servers that let AI agents read and write live finance data. The slides aren't theory, they're production.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Author of fifteen books on enterprise analytics">
          <p>The "Look Smarter Than You Are" series, written from 2007 to today, co-authored mostly with Tracy McMullen. Required reading inside a generation of finance and IT departments. Books that show up on bookshelves at the events Edward keynotes (sometimes the host doesn't realize that until the green room).</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Host of Asking Good Questions">
          <p>The podcast where Edward interviews CFOs, CEOs, and AI leaders about the questions that don't make it into LinkedIn posts. Co-chair of the Caribbean AI Summit 2026. President of the Puerto Rico AI Community (850+ executives and growing). He talks to your audience for a living, not just at them.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Signature Talks -->
  <Section title="Signature Talks" subtitle="Three keynotes, each ninety minutes by default, scalable up or down. Customized to your audience after the screening call." dark>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Answers to the Questions You've Been Quietly Asking Yourself About AI">
          <p>A keynote for executives who are tired of generic AI predictions and want frameworks for the questions they're already wrestling with privately. Drawn from a hundred-plus episodes of Asking Good Questions and a portfolio of live AI deployments. Works as a keynote, a fireside chat, or the opening session of a multi-day executive offsite.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">AI Strategy</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Executive Audience</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Keynote</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Fireside</span>
          </div>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Business Leaders Guide to AI">
          <p>AI is rewriting every process inside the company, from how finance closes the books to how marketing writes a brief to how engineering ships a feature. This keynote walks executives through what's actually changing, where to start (the highest-leverage pilots that won't blow up), and where to go next once the first wave lands. Built for leaders who have to make decisions on AI before they finish reading about it.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">AI Leadership</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Where to Start</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Decision-Making</span>
          </div>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Building a Company in the Era of AI">
          <p>Founded interRel at twenty-two. Ran it for twenty-five years. Merged it into a billion-dollar firm. Now building Caprus, an AI software and services company built for the Office of the CFO. A keynote for founders and operators on how building an organization changes when AI is rewriting the underlying business model.</p>
          <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Founders</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Operators</span>
            <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs font-[var(--font-mono)] dark:bg-white/5 dark:text-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 text-[var(--color-accent)]">Strategy</span>
          </div>
        </Card>
      </div>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- What You Get -->
  <Section title="What You Get" subtitle="When booking Edward, you're also booking an event campaign.">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="The Keynote">
          <p>One signature talk, customized to your audience after a working call with you (or your program chair). Includes a tech check the day before, a full rehearsal if you want one, and a Q&A or panel slot if it fits the format. Edward arrives early and stays for the hallway track.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="A Podcast Appearance">
          <p>An invited guest slot on Asking Good Questions, scheduled around your event. Your CEO or another C-level exec, your keynote, or a key customer of yours sits down with Edward for a conversation that goes out to the podcast audience and lives on Apple, Spotify, Amazon, and YouTube. Often runs the same week as the event.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <Card title="Thirty Days of Amplification">
          <p>If your event is public, a month of LinkedIn and X posts from Edward to a built-in audience of CFOs, CIOs, and AI operators. Event teasers before, recap takeaways after. Your event will also be mentioned for a month as a sponsor of Edward's YouTube posts, which reach an audience of over 200,000 subscribers.</p>
        </Card>
      </div>

    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- Inquiry Form + Screening Call -->
  <Section id="inquiry" dark>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12">

      <div class="animate-on-scroll">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4 dark:text-white text-[var(--color-primary)]" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">Speaking Inquiry</h2>
        <p class="dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)] mb-8">
          The more you tell Edward up front, the faster the screening call goes. Required fields are marked. Everything else helps him tailor the pitch.
        </p>

        <form action="https://api.web3forms.com/submit" method="POST" class="space-y-5"
          {...{"toolname": "speaking-inquiry-edward-roske", "tooldescription": "Submit a speaking engagement inquiry for Edward Roske. Use for keynote, fireside, workshop, or panel requests at conferences, corporate offsites, and executive events."}}>
          <input type="hidden" name="access_key" value="927fd498-3a0f-470c-89af-80a8558e8530" />
          <input type="hidden" name="subject" value="New speaking inquiry from roske.ai/speaking" />
          <input type="hidden" name="from_name" value="Speaking Inquiry" />
          <input type="hidden" name="redirect" value="https://roske.ai/speaking/?inquiry=received" />

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div>
              <label for="name" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Your name *</label>
              <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Email *</label>
              <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div>
              <label for="organization" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Organization *</label>
              <input type="text" id="organization" name="organization" required
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="event_name" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Event name *</label>
              <input type="text" id="event_name" name="event_name" required
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div>
              <label for="event_date" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Event date *</label>
              <input type="date" id="event_date" name="event_date" required
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="location" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Location *</label>
              <input type="text" id="location" name="location" required placeholder="City, country, or virtual"
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:placeholder-[var(--color-text-muted)]/40 dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] placeholder-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]/40 focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div>
              <label for="audience_size" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Expected audience size</label>
              <select id="audience_size" name="audience_size"
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
                <option value="">Select</option>
                <option value="under-50">Under 50</option>
                <option value="50-200">50 to 200</option>
                <option value="200-500">200 to 500</option>
                <option value="500-1500">500 to 1,500</option>
                <option value="1500+">1,500+</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="format" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Requested format</label>
              <select id="format" name="format"
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
                <option value="">Select</option>
                <option value="keynote">Keynote</option>
                <option value="fireside">Fireside chat</option>
                <option value="workshop">Workshop</option>
                <option value="panel">Panel</option>
                <option value="virtual">Virtual session</option>
                <option value="other">Other / not sure</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label for="audience_profile" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Audience profile</label>
            <input type="text" id="audience_profile" name="audience_profile" placeholder="CFOs, finance leaders, AI operators, founders, board members..."
              class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:placeholder-[var(--color-text-muted)]/40 dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] placeholder-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]/40 focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
          </div>

          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
            <div>
              <label for="budget" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Budget range</label>
              <select id="budget" name="budget"
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
                <option value="">Select</option>
                <option value="under-15k">Under $15K</option>
                <option value="15-25k">$15K to $25K</option>
                <option value="25-40k">$25K to $40K</option>
                <option value="40k+">$40K+</option>
                <option value="discuss">Prefer to discuss</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="event_url" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Event page (optional)</label>
              <input type="url" id="event_url" name="event_url" placeholder="https://"
                class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors
                  dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:placeholder-[var(--color-text-muted)]/40 dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] placeholder-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]/40 focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                  focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20" />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label for="notes" class="block text-sm font-medium mb-2 dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]">Notes</label>
            <textarea id="notes" name="notes" rows="4" placeholder="Theme of the event, what you want the audience to walk away with, anything Edward should know about the room..."
              class="w-full px-4 py-3 rounded-lg border transition-colors resize-y
                dark:bg-white/5 dark:border-[var(--color-border)] dark:text-white dark:placeholder-[var(--color-text-muted)]/40 dark:focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                bg-white border-[var(--color-border-light)] text-[var(--color-text-dark)] placeholder-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)]/40 focus:border-[var(--color-accent)]
                focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[var(--color-accent)]/20"></textarea>
          </div>

          <!-- Honeypot -->
          <div class="hidden">
            <input type="text" name="botcheck" />
          </div>

          <button type="submit"
            class="w-full px-6 py-3 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent)] text-white font-medium hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)] transition-all duration-200 hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
            Send Inquiry
          </button>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="animate-on-scroll rounded-xl p-6
          dark:bg-gradient-to-br dark:from-[var(--color-accent)]/[0.10] dark:to-white/[0.02] dark:border dark:border-[var(--color-accent)]/25
          bg-gradient-to-br from-[var(--color-accent)]/[0.08] to-white border border-[var(--color-accent)]/20">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2 dark:text-white text-[var(--color-primary)]" style="font-family: var(--font-heading);">Or book a screening call</h3>
          <p class="dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)] mb-5 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Thirty minutes with Edward. Walk through the event, the audience, the outcome you want. Leave with a recommended talk, a date hold, and a clean follow-up. Often faster than a back-and-forth over email.
          </p>
          <a href="/meet/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent)] text-white text-sm font-medium hover:bg-[var(--color-accent-hover)] transition-colors">
            Book Screening Call
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="animate-on-scroll rounded-xl p-6 dark:bg-white/[0.03] dark:border dark:border-white/[0.06] bg-white border border-black/[0.06]">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2 dark:text-white text-[var(--color-primary)]">Speaker one-pager</h3>
          <p class="dark:text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-[var(--color-text-dark-muted)] text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed">
